				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\epsilon $$\end{document}-greedy algorithm to unbias the search direction with a frequency of ϵ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\epsilon $$\end{document} = 0.3. We evaluate this approach in Sects. 5.1 and 5.2 to demonstrate the performance in the discovery of stable mixed-cation halide perovskites.Fig. 5
