In our study, as we are comparing parallel methods (FDI-BO, TOPK-BO) against the reference sequential BO, we utilize batch cycles to calculate the acceleration. In a single batch cycle, FDI-BO and TOPK-BO would execute k-DFT evaluations, while S-BO and random sampling will execute only 1-DFT evaluation. We modified the original AF formula to reflect this in Eq. (2):2AF=batch cycle to reach cut-off by (a)batch cycle to reach cut-off by (b)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
